text:
If you thought you can see extraordinary talent only on America’s Got Talent and similar shows, check out what Jimmy Fallon and Heidi Klum did on Tuesday.

The two of them danced together but their moves were determined by a dance move generator. As Fallon explained, “We’ll randomly select a never-before-seen dance move. Whoever’s turn it is has to make up a dance for that move. The best dancer wins.”

The two stars danced to “Invisible Hula Hoop,” “Fork in the Garbage Disposal,” “Speed Bowling,” “Mom Tries Hip-Hop,” “Eggs ‘N Bacon”. Hard to imagine? Watch the video below.
title: Jimmy Fallon and Heidi Klum Compete in a Hilarious Dance Battle
